‚úÖ Correct Approaches
1Ô∏è‚É£ Brute Force Approach (Using String)
Idea

Convert number to string

Reverse string

Convert back to number

Handle sign and overflow

Pseudocode
if x < 0:
    sign = -1
else:
    sign = 1

x = abs(x)
reverse string of x
result = sign * reversed number

if result out of 32-bit range:
    return 0
return result

JavaScript Code
var reverse = function(x) {
    let sign = x < 0 ? -1 : 1;
    let rev = Number(String(Math.abs(x)).split('').reverse().join('')) * sign;

    if (rev < -(2**31) || rev > (2**31 - 1)) return 0;
    return rev;
};

Time & Space Complexity

Time: O(n) (digits)

Space: O(n)

2Ô∏è‚É£ Better / Optimal Approach (Math ‚Äì No String)
Idea

Extract last digit using % 10

Build reversed number using multiplication

Handle overflow during construction

Pseudocode
rev = 0
while x != 0:
    digit = x % 10
    x = trunc(x / 10)
    rev = rev * 10 + digit

    if rev out of range:
        return 0
return rev

JavaScript Code (Best Approach)
var reverse = function(x) {
    let rev = 0;

    while (x !== 0) {
        let digit = x % 10;
        x = Math.trunc(x / 10);

        rev = rev * 10 + digit;

        if (rev < -(2**31) || rev > (2**31 - 1)) {
            return 0;
        }
    }
    return rev;
};

Time & Space Complexity

Time: O(n)

Space: O(1) ‚úÖ

üî• Summary
Approach	Uses String	Space	Recommended
Brute Force	Yes	O(n)	‚ùå
